This paper discusses the publication process and editorial oversight of a megajournal, which is relevant to the digital libraries (cs.DL) sub-category. The analysis of editor activity and manuscript bias involves computational methods, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). The study also examines citation patterns, which could relate to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
